@Apaseall Since Kopernicus 1.3.0-6 or soon after that, Kopernicus uses the body name (and deprecated FlightGlobalsIndex) to allow vessel location to persist when you swap planet mods. As long as the particular planet (by its name and not a computed number) still exists, everything you left there will still be there. OPM being moved by the addition or removal or other planet packs won't threaten your ships in OPM SOIs...... There is no gameplay threat to Science or Sandbox mode, but Career mode progression will break. The contracts system will get confused. Also, KSS is or has been fully incompatible with Sigma Dimensions.

Edited August 17, 2018 by JadeOfMaar
